post_text: As we anticipate the arrival of our students and staff for the 2020-2021 school year, Aquilla ISD has partnered with Belfor Restoration to complete a detailed 3-Step Clean System that uses advanced technology that provides a surface protectant on all surfaces which provide a 90 day barrier of protection that renders microorganisms inactive once they hit the treated surfaces. Our entire facility including our bus fleet have been treated with this 3-Step Clean System. Aquilla ISD is the only school district in Hill County to have this certified seal that provides this level of protection for all individuals that enter our facility. #together

post_text: School districts across Texas are struggling to answer one question: What will school be like next year because of COVID-19? Our intent is to reopen and and allow students to return to some semblance of normalcy and routine as school resumes in the fall. As we prepare for the return of students in the fall, please help us make appropriate plans for student safety by sharing your concerns and questions about the upcoming school year by completing our "Return to School" survey by Sunday, June 28th. https://zfrmz.com/e9TbcsLMw02hRiKElGmg

Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families can receive application instructions using the link below. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.
P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

ESC Region 12
May 8 at 8:22 PM 路

Even when life is interrupted by a global pandemic, life is still happening. We still have homes to run, we still have to find things we need. We're trying to keep our families together, yet safely apart and we're trying to keep our kids learning when their school buildings stand silent. In this brief conversation, we'll explore what keeps us together as parents and educators and discuss what we have to guard against from ripping us apart. We're not necessarily experiencing it like everyone else. But one thing is for certain; we're all experiencing it. We're living through the same storm, but experiencing it in a different boat. Contact: Jeni Janek - jjanek@esc12.net

Aquilla Family,

We are sad to announce that due to these unprecedented times dealing with COVID-19, Varsity Spirit has decided to cancel the Varsity Spirit Awards competition. Our amazing mascot, MAC the Cougar, was a finalist for this award for the second year in a row. Although he may not have the opportunity to bring home the trophy this year we know that he is by far the best mascot there is! He goes above and beyond in everything he does and he is number one in our hearts. We are so blessed and thankful to have him as our AISD mascot! Please feel free to leave a note in the comments section to share your love and support for MAC.

We love you MAC!!

Coach Penard and Aquilla Cheer

SCHOLARSHIPS and CAMPUS TOURS

All local scholarships have been uploaded to the COVID 19 tab on the Aquilla ISD website. Seniors, please continue to keep working on your scholarships and getting them turned in by their deadline. A few scholarship deadlines have changed or are pending.

Students needing transcripts for these scholarships need to email Garla Montez at garla.montez@aquillaisd.net by Sunday, March 28. Transcripts will be available to pick up on Monday, March 30, between 10:00 am - 12:00 pm. at the school.

If a scholarship requires recommendation letters from school personnel, you will need to reach out to them via email as soon as possible and they should be able to email a recommendation letter back to you for your scholarship application.

www.fastweb.com & www.cappex.com

Two great websites for any student who would like to take a virtual tour of a college:

www.campustours.com & www.youvisit.com/collegesearch/

post_text: Good evening Cougar family, we have an update on our boys basketball playoff scenario. We are currently in a 3 way tie for second and third place with Covington and Blum. Per UIL rules, a three way tie is determined by a play-intournament between the three teams. We have drawn for seeding in the bracket and received the first round bye. Covington and Blum will play on Thursday the 20th at 6pm in Morgan. The winner of that will play Us (Aquilla) on Friday at 6pm in Morgan. The result of the game Friday will determine the 2nd place team and either the third place team or the playback on Saturday for third place. Come out and support your Courgars Friday night 6pm in Morgan as we work to clinch our playoff spot.

REMINDER!

***JH GAME CHANGE***

Due to multiple student athletes participating in UIL events on Thursday Jan. 16th, we have moved the Jr High Basketball games scheduled that day to Monday Jan 13. We apologize for any inconvenience this may have caused, but we felt this was the best fit to help accommodate all student athletes participating. Thank you for your understanding and support.
